    "body": "> When using the --web flag, the validator client can generate a random auth token and log it to stdout + write it to a file to persist it\r\n\r\nIf a logging mechanism and file are used for token delivery you need to be sure that:\r\n- the file has permissions 0600\r\n-  token will not be logged into a log file readable for anyone\r\n\r\nSuch bugs were found in Lighthouse:\r\n- https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/issues/2438\r\n- https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/issues/2437",
